President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Steve A. Linick as Inspector General of the Federal Housing Finance Agency and Thomas Hicks as Commissioner of the Election Assistance Commission. Linick is currently serving as the Executive Director of the National Procurement Fraud Task Force at the Department of Justice and the Deputy Chief of the Fraud Section, Criminal Division of the Department of Justice. Hicks has been the Senior Elections Counsel on the U.S. House of Representatives Committee on House Administration since 2003.